Polish Zloty Drops to Weakest in 3 Months, Stocks Fall on Europe

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-07-12T07:14:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/polish-zloty-drops-to-weakest-in-3-months-stocks-fall-on-europe.html
The zloty dropped to the weakest
level in more than three months and banks led Polish stocks
lower amid concern  Europe ’s debt crisis will worsen.  The zloty dropped 1.2 percent to 4.0322 per euro as of 9:06
a.m. in Warsaw, the weakest intraday level since April 5. The
benchmark  stock index  slid 1.1 percent to 2,714.08 as PKO Bank
Polski SA and Bank Pekao SA, Poland’s two largest lenders,
retreated.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  